rom the ECE department’s curriculum, faculty expertise, peer support, and culture of excellence.  Within the past five years, we have graduated 436 master’s students and 52 doctoral students in electrical and computer engineering. Here is a representative sample of the places in industry and academia where they headed after UIC:       Industry roles         Alico Systems Inc.  Allegro MicroSystems  Allston Trading LLC  Alperian Noninvasive Diagnostics  Amazon  Amazon Web Services  Amphenol T&M Antennas  Ansys  Army Research Labs  Binachip  BroadCom  Cadence Design Systems  Caterpillar  Cisco Systems  Citigroup  CNH America  Coval Systems Inc.  Delphi  Delta Mobile Software  Eagle 7 Trading  Enphase Energy  EPIR Technologies  Freescale Semiconductor  Fujitsu R&D  GE Research  General Dynamics  General MEMS Corp.  Global Foundries US  Google  Huawei  iKoa  Imec USA Nanoelectronics Design Center  Integra Technologies  Intel  International Rectifier  Intuitive Surgical            IntuVision  Lemko Corporation  LHV Power Corp.  Litepoint  Makro Technology  MathWorks  Mattson Technologies  Max Linear  Mayo Clinic  Methode Electronics  Microsoft  Motorola Mobility  Motorola Solutions  Novellus  Nvidia  Phillips  Progress Finance  Qualcomm  Quant  Rehabilitation Institute of Chicago  Samsung Austin Semiconductor  Sandia National Laboratory  Sandisk  Seagate R&D  Schlumberger  Siemens  Skyworks Inc.  Space Systems / LORAL  Space Systems Loral  Telephonics  Teradyne  Trident Microsystems  Varian Medical Systems  Videojet Technologies  Western Digital  Xerox           Academic positions and further study:    Columbia University  Istanbul Technical University  Izmir Institute of Technology  Johns Hopkins University  McMaster University  Mustafa Kemal University, Turkey  National Institutes of Health  National University of Ireland  New York University  Northwestern University  Notre Dame University  Ohio State University  Pennsylvania State University  Princeton University  Sta